From b626118f1dd7bc3dd2391ef2449e4acc21c2c2c9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Haofeng Li <lihaofeng@kylinos.cn>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 19:41:39 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] ksmbd: fix out-of-bounds read in ksmbd_compare_user()

ksmbd_compare_user() compares passkeys with u1->passkey_sz as the
memcmp() length. Each passkey buffer is allocated from the hash size
returned for that login response, so the second user's passkey can be
shorter than u1->passkey_sz.

An authenticated client can drive the vulnerable comparison by reusing an
existing SMB2 session. The first session setup stores sess->user from a
login response supplied by the ksmbd userspace daemon. A later session
setup reauthentication, or Kerberos session reuse, allocates a fresh user
object for the same account and compares it with sess->user. If the
daemon or authentication backend returns a shorter hash_sz for the later
login response, ksmbd_compare_user(sess->user, user) uses the old, larger
size and memcmp() reads past the end of the new passkey buffer.

Reject users with different passkey sizes before comparing buffers,
matching destroy_previous_session().

Fixes: a58b45a4dbfd ("ksmbd: set RSS capable in FSCTL_QUERY_NETWORK_INTERFACE_INFO")
Signed-off-by: Haofeng Li <lihaofeng@kylinos.cn>
Reviewed-by: ChenXiaoSong <chenxiaosong@kylinos.cn>
---
 fs/smb/server/mgmt/user_config.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/smb/server/mgmt/user_config.c b/fs/smb/server/mgmt/user_config.c
index cf45841d9d1b..221888306d48 100644
--- a/fs/smb/server/mgmt/user_config.c
+++ b/fs/smb/server/mgmt/user_config.c
@@ -93,6 +93,8 @@ bool ksmbd_compare_user(struct ksmbd_user *u1, struct ksmbd_user *u2)
 {
 	if (strcmp(u1->name, u2->name))
 		return false;
+	if (u1->passkey_sz != u2->passkey_sz)
+		return false;
 	if (memcmp(u1->passkey, u2->passkey, u1->passkey_sz))
 		return false;
 
